 issued a statement with a similar apology, admitting that he sometimes forgets to wear a seat belt and needs to remind himself to always buckle up. Copyright 2007 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed. Cianci expected to be released to halfway house tomorrow R.I. elders now have a place to turn for after-hours help Two suspects in supermarket "pin pad" scam plead guilty Target 12 Investigators: Pet Dangers Free Comic Book Day in Rhode Island Alabama formally apologizes for slavery TB patient in Denver for treatment Bush calls on 15 countries to set global emission goal by 2008 I Want My Car Looking for a New or Used car? Let local dealers compete for your business!! Local Entertainment- IMAX - Eye on RI Your #1 Source for Local & National Entertainment Not to Be Forgotten Eyewitness News&#39; unique series of stories that focus on forgotten local people. Create traditional crafts that my grandmother and mother used to do many years ago. Daily, weekly and monthly horoscopes for life, love, work and more! Planning a party? Or maybe just in the mood for a special snack ... you&#39;ll love these tasty recipes. Send questions and comments about this website to the All content &copy; Copyright 2003-2007 WorldNow, WPRI, WNAC and Associated Press. All Rights Reserved. For more information on this site, please read our
