http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/12-3&fd=R&url=http://www.wpbf.com/news/13411392/detail.html&cid=1116758582&ei=muxeRqKEDZGoqwPX6vjNDQ Lake Okeechobee Hits Record Low Due To Drought - News Story - WPBF West Palm Beach Seen On The Scene PB Gardens Brush Fire Phase 1 Restrictions Info Phase 2 Restrictions Info Lake Okeechobee Hits Record Low Due To Drought POSTED: 10:15 am EDT May 30, 2007 UPDATED: 9:58 am EDT Up for Breaking News Alerts WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. -- Lake Okeechobee's water levels has hit a record low due to a drought. The South Florida Water Management District reported today a record low of just under nine feet, surpassing the mark set during a 2001 drought. The region's drought is leading water managers to assess how to best protect drinking water supplies, meet needs of the important agriculture industry and protect natural resources. The average water level should be around 13 feet this time of year in the second-largest freshwater lake in the contiguous United States. The record low is the result of months of lower-than-normal rainfall levels that have afflicted the main backup water supply for 5 million South Florida residents. Lake Okeechobee is also the liquid heart of the Everglades. . The Associated Press contributed to this report. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed. Top Employers For Working Mothers You can have the best of both worlds. Check out which companies do the most to help working mothers. Tips For Moving With Your Pet Whether you're moving across town or across the country, find out what you need to know about moving with your pet. Keep Your Car From Being Stolen Even a car that looks rough can be a target for thieves. Find out how to keep your car from being damaged or stolen. Thinking Of Getting A Time Share? Find out if it's a sound investment or a quick way to throw your money away. Like video? Click over and check out our new video page we call Links We Like in